## ⚠️ Anti-Patterns

| ❌ NEVER | ✅ ALWAYS | Why |
|---------|-----------|-----|
| `String` dans handlers | `&str` ou `Arc<str>` | Évite allocations |
| `unwrap()` en prod | `Result<T, E>` + `?` | Error handling propre |
| `Clone` sur AppState | `Arc<AppState>` | Shared state efficace |
| `Box<dyn Error>` | Error enum + `thiserror` | Type-safe errors |
| Routes imbriquées | `Router::nest()` | Structure claire |
| Blocking dans async | `spawn_blocking` | Ne bloque runtime |
| `println!` pour logging | `tracing::info!`, `tracing::error!` | Structured logging |
| String concatenation pour SQL | `sqlx::query_as!` macro | Compile-time verification |
| `Vec<u8>` pour binary data | `bytes::Bytes` | Zero-copy parsing |
| Raw mutex locks | `tokio::sync::RwLock` | Async-safe locking |

---

## 🔧 Troubleshooting

| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| "the trait bound is not satisfied" | Type manquant dans State | Ajouter `Clone` + `Send` |
| "future cannot be sent between threads" | Type non `Send` | Utiliser `Arc` ou `spawn_blocking` |
| "borrowed value does not live long enough" | Lifetime trop court | Vérifier les références |
| "ambiguous item" | Import conflict | Préfixer avec le module |
| "no method named \`json\`" | Feature manquante | Activer `axum/json` dans Cargo.toml |
| **"Future cannot be sent between threads safely"** | Missing `Send` bound | Use `#[tokio::main]` and check types |
| **"Borrowed value does not live long enough"** | Lifetime issue in handler | Clone or use `Arc<T>` |
| **"Database connection closed"** | Pool exhausted | Increase `max_connections` or check connection leaks |
| **"Trait bound not satisfied"** | Missing trait import | Add `use async_trait::async_trait;` |
| **"SQL query wrong"** | Using `query!` instead of `query_as!` | Use `query_as!` for type mapping |
| **"CORS error in browser"** | Missing CORS layer | Add `CorsLayer` to router |
| **"Service not found"** | Wrong state setup | Use `.with_state(app_state)` on router |
| **"Migration failed"** | Wrong migration path | Check `migrate!("./migrations")` path |
| **"Compile time too long"** | Too many dependencies in one crate | Split into workspace crates |
| **"Handler not called"** | Wrong route order | More specific routes first |

